-- Knight Capital obtains financing at $1.50 a share: CNBC
-- 
-- Sun Aug 5, 2012 8:56pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/08/06/us-knightcapital-funding-idUSBRE87501I20120806

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Knight Capital Group Inc has obtained $400 million in rescue funding from four firms through a convertible preferred offering at $1.50 per share, CNBC reported on Sunday without citing sources. 
 The news service earlier reported that Knight Capital was close to securing $400 million from a group of investors that was likely to include Chicago market maker Getco and Omaha brokerage firm TD Ameritrade. (Reporting by  Soyoung Kim  and  Katya Wachtel )